<span id="freeTextContainer13287431302670008046">A Socratic fist in a velvet glove.<br/><br/>A couple of incredibly friendly Cthulhus travel to Earth, almost obliterate mankind because they can&apos;t find them, then finds them, and they have an improbably-sized sit-down chat. The giants are then used as a vehicle to shittalk a handful of philosophers that Voltaire was not big into. Everyone ultimately quotes Op Ivy. &quot;All I know is I don&apos;t know nothin&apos;.&quot; <br/><br/>1752? Really? It&apos;s wittier, more accessible, and of greater clarity than most sci-fi you&apos;ll stumble into </span>
  <span id="freeText13287431302670008046" style="display:none">A Socratic fist in a velvet glove.<br /><br />A couple of incredibly friendly Cthulhus travel to Earth, almost obliterate mankind because they can't find them, then finds them, and they have an improbably-sized sit-down chat. The giants are then used as a vehicle to shittalk a handful of philosophers that Voltaire was not big into. Everyone ultimately quotes Op Ivy. "All I know is I don't know nothin'." <br /><br />1752? Really? It's wittier, more accessible, and of greater clarity than most sci-fi you'll stumble into today. <br /><br />Can we canonize Voltaire?</span>
