  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2563272263" />
    <a title="Noah Goats" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41735508-noah-goats"><img alt="Noah Goats" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1526489093p2/41735508.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2563272263?book_show_action=true">Oct 17, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Noah Goats" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Noah Goats" href="/user/show/41735508-noah-goats">Noah Goats</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback " href="/book/show/1423467.Microm_gas">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2563272263" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7434615645245134833">Micromegas is a fun little science fiction story by Voltaire. It tells the story of an enormous alien from Sirius who visits our solar system where he meets up with a not quite as tall alien from Saturn and the two of them pay a visit to the Earth. The book is a satire that drives home the point that humans are full of more pride and pretense than our small place in the universe can reasonably justify. It’s simply written and pretty easy to understand in the original French even if you are not a</span>
  <span id="freeText7434615645245134833" style="display:none">Micromegas is a fun little science fiction story by Voltaire. It tells the story of an enormous alien from Sirius who visits our solar system where he meets up with a not quite as tall alien from Saturn and the two of them pay a visit to the Earth. The book is a satire that drives home the point that humans are full of more pride and pretense than our small place in the universe can reasonably justify. It’s simply written and pretty easy to understand in the original French even if you are not a native French speaker.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7434615645245134833" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


