    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_523513859" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/523513859" />
    <a title="Pramod Pant" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16966766-pramod-pant"><img alt="Pramod Pant" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599718150p2/16966766.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/523513859?book_show_action=true">Feb 01, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pramod Pant" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pramod Pant" href="/user/show/16966766-pramod-pant">Pramod Pant</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer523513859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17233670609512866866">Inimitable Voltaire in humour and style. &apos;Mircromegas&apos; is a creature from outer space who along with a Saturnian, visits earth and finds life here. They are both extremely large, Micromegas being much larger than the Saturnian. Their intellects and senses are proportionately complex. After finding humans, they enter into a dialogue with them. <br/><br/>The funny and instructive part is that the cocksure earthlings commit the error of being too sure of themselves as their frame of reference is limited and </span>
  <span id="freeText17233670609512866866" style="display:none">Inimitable Voltaire in humour and style. 'Mircromegas' is a creature from outer space who along with a Saturnian, visits earth and finds life here. They are both extremely large, Micromegas being much larger than the Saturnian. Their intellects and senses are proportionately complex. After finding humans, they enter into a dialogue with them. <br /><br />The funny and instructive part is that the cocksure earthlings commit the error of being too sure of themselves as their frame of reference is limited and factually flawed. Voltaire has used this device of differing stature (scalar, sensory and intellectual) very cunningly and effectively. <br /><br />A must read for all as it shows how fallible we are, not only in the France of Voltaire, but everywhere and always. <br /><br />Though it should not be part of this review, still I recommend two more books by Voltaire- 'Candide' and 'Zadig'. Both bring out the folly of treating commonly held notions which boast only of the support of tradition and can not of reason. <br /><br />Brilliantly Voltaire, and a must read for all. It is timeless. And yours. Grab it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17233670609512866866" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

